  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Staphylococcus aureus nasal carriage is a major risk factor of infection with this
      bacterium. Staphylococcus aureus colonization of the posterior nasal cavity is still
      misunderstood. This study is aimed at evaluating the relationship between Staphylococcus
      aureus strains colonizing the vestibulum nasi, the sphenoethmoidal recess and the
      nasopharynx.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
